		<title>17INDUSTRY</title>
		<content>  In the past the local industry       
 consisted of cotton spinning and coal 
 mining, with minor operations         
 involving lime burning and brick      
 making.                               
  The picture today is radically       
 different, with only one textile mill 
 left in operation, half way between   
 Marple Bridge and Mellor, and all the 
 mines shut down and the lime kilns    
 derelict.                             
  There is no major industrial employer
 in the district today, but there are  
 several small concerns undertaking a  
 variety of tasks mainly for the local 
 area.                                 
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
